	used for place bug; this time without breaking escape key.

2005-10-15  Dominik Vogt  <dominik(dot)vogt(at)gmx(dot)de>

	* fvwm/move_resize.c (__move_loop):
	removed the previous patch as it breaks aborting window motion with the
	escape key.

2005-10-03  Viktor Griph  <griph(at)dd(dot)chalmers(dot)se>

	* fvwm/move_resize.c (__move_loop):
	fixed bug where finishing movment with keyboard would set a random
	button as used for placement.

2005-09-30  Viktor Griph  <griph(at)dd(dot)chalmers(dot)se>

	* NEWS
	* fvwm/frame.c (frame_setup_border):
	reverted change for move of window parts (reset of PressedW).

2005-09-29  Dominik Vogt  <dominik(dot)vogt(at)gmx(dot)de>

	* fvwm/frame.c (frame_setup_border):
	fixed a Warning

2005-09-29  Viktor Griph  <griph(at)dd(dot)chalmers(dot)se>

	* NEWS:
	* fvwm/move_resize.c (__resize_window):
	removed duplicate pointer query for enter/leave notify events.
	resizing of shaded windows in the shaded direction no longer
	results in bogus ref points.

	* fvwm/frame.c (frame_setup_border):
	reset PressedW if the part has moved. This prevents strange
	ref points in resize if called from some complex functions.

	* fvwm/frame.c (frame_create_move_resize_args):
	shaded windows use get_client_geometry for client geometry.

